    <Paragraph FontSize="22">Legacy Issues
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph>Toggle Pattern will only be supported when the Win32 menu item is checked and can be programmatically determined necessary to support Toggle Pattern. Because the Win32 menu item does not expose whether it has the ability to be checked, Invoke Pattern will be supported when the menu item is not checked. An exception will be made to always support Invoke Pattern even for menu items that should only support Toggle Pattern. This is so clients do not become confused that an element that was supporting Invoke Pattern (when menu item was unchecked) no longer supports the pattern once it becomes checked.
    </Paragraph>

